Visual Overhaul Walkthrough
I have completely revamped the Janggi game with a new "Royal Court" theme.

🎨 Visual Changes
1. Royal Court Theme (CSS/UI)
Background: A deep, radial gradient (Dark Slate to Black) provides a premium atmosphere.
Glassmorphism: The game panel now uses a frosted glass effect (backdrop-filter: blur) to blend seamlessly with the background.
Typography: Integrated Noto Serif KR for a traditional yet modern look.
2. Premium Board Rendering (Canvas)
Wood Texture: The board now features a generated wood grain gradient (#e6c288 to #b08d55).
Engraved Grid: Grid lines now have a slight shadow/highlight to appear "carved" into the wood.
Palace Decoration: The Palace (Gung) area uses bolder lines and corner accents.
3. 3D Stone Pieces (Canvas)
Esthetic: Pieces now look like polished stones with:
Gradient Body: Off-white/ivory radial gradients.
Beveled Edge: Double-ring border for a 3D effect.
Drop Shadow: Soft shadow to lift pieces off the board.
Typography: Characters are rendered with an "engraved" shallow shadow effect.
✨ New Mechanics
Smooth Animations
Movement: Pieces no longer teleport. They slide smoothly to their destination using a Cubic Ease-Out function.
Visual Feedback:
Valid Moves: Indicated by glowing blue dots (#29b6f6).
Selection: The selected piece glows with a distinct blue aura.
